<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2022-01-20 15:33:57.037007</lastBuildDate><item><title>Its gona be a good day</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ph6Pff0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tKOCj6O.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DsIWeYC.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LqersuX.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gWCfoFm.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ph6Pff0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[baals]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>i love reading things like this</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/U423Xd1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8TMnvxR.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>and i figured so would you</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/U423Xd1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reformedxile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>BreadBox</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/x9lNV5M</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HGVNoVZ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>link in first pic https://twitter.com/i/events/1158751367151775745</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f17Sghg.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/x9lNV5M</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[IWillDrawOnYourPictures]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I did a thing. 215 to 130 lbs</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Y217K3R</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/G2BqJFv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So this is me today at 130 lbs! Losing weight is so damn hard but I finally feel good when I look in the mirror. I have sacrificed my body twice being pregnant and it definitely took it's toll on my body and confidence. The heaviest I reached was 215 lbs when I was pregnant with my second child and I absolutely hated what I saw in the mirror.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VhnflAi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2 months ago at 143.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pGWjOTW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is 6 months after my daughter was born. I used the elliptical every day for atleast an hour and watched everything I ate. I was 185 and nothing was working. I was so depressed but stayed optimistic.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AvLnxsv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is me before getting pregnant with my daughter and I was 190(plus) lbs and I may have seemed happy to everyone on the outside but I was struggling internally every day with how my body looked. I  love my children and they are my whole world but pregnancy is bitch on your body. I finally feel like I have myself back and I'm so beyond happy about it. 

To any woman struggling with their body after pregnancy, I feel your pain and frustration. It has been a long bumpy road to get to this point. To anyone struggling with their weight, there is always hope. You can do it!

I eat healthy and exercise as much as I can (hard to do while managing two tiny humans) but the main thing I learned through this all is to allow yourself to have cheat days. Eat a damn donut once in a while or big bowl of ice cream and don't hate yourself for it. But most importantly never give up on yourself. 
We all have one life and it is best to make the most of it. Thank you for letting me share this experience with you all!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Y217K3R</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[aticklepickle]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hey, Doc...tell us how you really feel</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9rgh0Sf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LyJ9n19.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9rgh0Sf</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reformedxile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Demonstration of Inca whistling vessels mimicking animal sounds</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/4yfaKfG</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/X4VWLvb.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Using only the flow of water, these Ancient Inca whistling vessels known as 'huascos' mimic various animal calls. These ancient ceramic whistling bottles have been dated as far back at ca. 500  BC</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/4yfaKfG</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ALittleDistantShiningStar]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Indigenous Beauty</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2aqBedE</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ahmaz60.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Ahsaki Baa LaFrance-Chachere created America’s 1st Indigenous Black-owned and operated prestige beauty brand on the Navajo Nation reservation where she grew up. Her cosmetics and skincare line, Ah-Shí Beauty, is founded on principles of inclusivity – and gratitude for her Native American roots.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2aqBedE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[60SecondDocs]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Don't scream...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yZNK9pr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt